Constantly cycling through new matter.

08:44.100 --> 08:44.460
Exactly.

08:44.980 --> 08:50.980
The actual water droplets that make up the storm on Monday are completely gone and replaced by new ocean water by Wednesday.

08:51.480 --> 08:54.760
The hurricane has zero material continuity.

08:55.020 --> 08:55.640
None whatsoever.

08:56.140 --> 09:00.760
So if I look at Flyxion's framework, it seems to imply that the hurricane's identity is entirely relative.

09:01.140 --> 09:05.000
It's only an object depending on what kind of transformation it's subjected to.

09:05.000 --> 09:09.500
What's fascinating here is that a hurricane is the perfect empirical model for this.

09:09.800 --> 09:12.460
In classical thought, identity is absolute, right?

09:12.540 --> 09:13.580
A thing is what it is.

09:13.640 --> 09:14.500
A table is a table.

09:14.580 --> 09:14.740
Right.

09:15.100 --> 09:21.940
But Flyxion demonstrates mathematically that identity is deeply relative, specifically to a designated family of transformations.

09:22.440 --> 09:23.300
Let's look at your hurricane.

09:23.500 --> 09:23.700
Okay.

09:23.700 --> 09:29.100
Its identity easily survives the transformation of, say, continuous water molecule replacement.

09:29.260 --> 09:30.020
Because they shape holes.

09:30.260 --> 09:30.440
Yes.

09:30.780 --> 09:34.340
It also survives the transformation of moving across the Atlantic Ocean.

09:34.740 --> 09:42.620
But if it hits land, and you subject it to the transformation of removing the thermal energy of the ocean, the pattern shatters.

09:42.840 --> 09:44.120
It stops being a hurricane.

09:44.360 --> 09:45.380
It just becomes rain.

09:45.480 --> 09:45.820
Yes.

09:46.220 --> 09:50.340
The hurricane only has identity relative to the transformations it can actually survive.

09:51.240 --> 09:52.760
Flyxion applies this everywhere.

09:52.760 --> 09:53.740
Like in biology.

09:54.120 --> 09:54.400
Exactly.

