Happens to the best of us.

13:12.500 --> 13:12.740
Right.

13:13.040 --> 13:17.080
When you pull it out, it's just a crumpled, water-damaged mess.

13:17.720 --> 13:18.560
The ink is bleeding.

13:18.920 --> 13:20.040
The paper is degraded.

13:20.440 --> 13:23.680
The physical invariance of that piece of paper is utterly destroyed.

13:23.920 --> 13:26.580
It is not the same arrangement of atoms it was yesterday?

13:26.720 --> 13:26.860
No.

13:27.260 --> 13:29.740
So classical invariance says the object is gone.

13:29.740 --> 13:30.120
Right.

