Now, that DNA wasn't perfectly invariant either, right?

15:25.460 --> 15:26.820
No, it was heavily fragmented.

15:27.480 --> 15:34.280
It had specific patterns of chemical damage, like cytosine deamination, which actually proved it was ancient.

15:34.500 --> 15:38.060
But modern genomic sequencing acted as a massive reconstruction operator.

15:38.220 --> 15:43.740
It took those fragmented traces, aligned them against known human reference genomes, and rebuilt the distinction.

15:44.160 --> 15:48.400
They could tell exactly which ancient hunter-gatherer clade those artists belonged to.

15:48.760 --> 15:49.860
The creators are dead.

15:50.100 --> 15:51.100
The event is over.

15:51.100 --> 15:52.700
The physical medium is ruined.

15:52.940 --> 16:02.620
But the distinction, the specific genetic sequence that differentiated those humans from others survived because an admissible reconstruction procedure existed.

16:03.180 --> 16:05.800
So existence over time is not about physical endurance.

16:05.960 --> 16:07.720
