36:17.160 --> 36:22.460
This brings us to the final, and arguably the most technically demanding and profound, section of the monograph.

36:23.140 --> 36:30.880
Flyxion takes this entire framework of recoverable distinction and turns it outward, applying it to the ultimate nature of existence, space-time, and causality.

36:31.220 --> 36:32.220
Let's start with reality.

36:32.560 --> 36:38.940
If objects are just temporary bundles of surviving distinctions, and identity is relative, what is actually real?

36:39.180 --> 36:42.120
Reality is not a physical catalog of stuff.

36:42.120 --> 36:44.060
You cannot put reality in a box.

36:44.540 --> 36:50.180
Fiction defines reality operationally as the domain of persistent constraint.

36:50.460 --> 36:51.360
Persistent constraint.

36:51.460 --> 36:52.820
It is whatever pushes back.

36:53.260 --> 36:57.360
It is whatever refuses or restricts our attempts at reconstruction.

36:57.460 --> 36:58.320
Refusal of reconstruction.

36:58.320 --> 37:07.060
So if I try to walk through a solid brick wall, the physical properties of the wall refuse my body's attempt to reconstruct my spatial coordinates on the other side of it.

37:07.100 --> 37:07.840
They block you.

37:07.840 --> 37:11.480
That refusal, that hard mathematical constraint, is reality.

37:11.480 --> 37:12.480
Precisely.

37:12.480 --> 37:17.120
If there were no constraints in the universe, any transformation would be instantly possible.

37:17.120 --> 37:21.380
You could reconstruct a lump of coal into a block of gold with zero effort.

37:21.380 --> 37:26.160
The universe would just be infinite, featureless chaos, and alignment would be meaningless.

37:26.580 --> 37:29.440
Reality is the structural resistance of the universe.

37:29.940 --> 37:36.920
And existence, what it means to actually be a thing, is simply persistent admissibility within those constraints.

37:36.920 --> 37:38.740
Persistent admissibility.

37:38.740 --> 37:52.180
You exist because the intricate web of universal constraints currently permits your specific biological and structural distinctions to be continuously reconstructed from one second to the next.

37:52.320 --> 37:53.740
You fit into the allowed parameters.

37:54.560 --> 37:56.380
You are allowed to exist by the constraints.

37:56.380 --> 38:00.840
Yes. You are an admissible trajectory through the constraint space.

38:01.440 --> 38:10.020
But to understand trajectory, we have to look at Flyxion's definition of time, which is a radical departure from both classical physics and common intuition.

38:10.260 --> 38:11.280
Oh, time. Yeah.

38:11.580 --> 38:15.940
Time is not a dimension we are traveling through, it is not a container, and it is not a flowing river.

38:16.100 --> 38:18.280
This part forced me to reread it multiple times.

38:18.800 --> 38:21.580
If time isn't a dimension we move through, what is it?

38:21.580 --> 38:26.740
Time is the irreversible accumulation of constraint into a reconstruction history.

38:26.880 --> 38:28.400
Time is accumulated constraint.

38:28.700 --> 38:31.500
Okay, I need to push back on this from a standard physics perspective.

38:31.520 --> 38:31.900
Okay, four.

38:32.380 --> 38:35.420
In Einstein's relativity, we often talk about the block universe.

38:35.420 --> 38:40.260
