38:40.940 --> 38:42.020
Time is just a coordinate.

38:42.680 --> 38:45.660
How does Flyxion reconcile that with time being an accumulation?

38:46.160 --> 38:50.640
This raises an important question about the intersection of epistemology and physics.

38:50.640 --> 38:59.280
This section argues the block universe is a mathematical abstraction that totally ignores the reconstructive asymmetry of reality.

38:59.840 --> 39:00.140
Meaning what?

39:00.740 --> 39:03.540
Why does the past feel fixed and unchangeable?

39:03.940 --> 39:11.300
Because, in Flyxion's model, the constraints of past events have already been incorporated into the structural geometry of the universe.

39:11.520 --> 39:12.400
They are locked in.

39:12.540 --> 39:13.340
They are the foundation.

39:13.740 --> 39:16.040
They are the conditions upon which the present is built.

39:16.220 --> 39:17.860
Why does the future feel open?

39:17.860 --> 39:25.440
Because the future consists merely of admissible continuations that have not yet been subjected to the incorporation of constraint.

39:25.800 --> 39:26.300
And the present.

39:26.700 --> 39:27.600
Where are we right now?

39:27.960 --> 39:31.000
The present is not a location on a geometric timeline.

39:31.500 --> 39:32.840
The present is an operation.

39:33.280 --> 39:33.640
An operation.

39:33.880 --> 39:38.720
It is the active boundary where admissibility is converted into incorporated constraint.

39:39.200 --> 39:42.620
The present is the absolute edge of universal reconstruction.

39:42.620 --> 39:44.320
That is staggering.

39:44.820 --> 39:50.280
The universe is literally computing itself into existence at the boundary of the present, logging in constraints.

39:50.680 --> 39:57.780
And our biological brains experience that continuous incorporation as the subjective feeling of time passing.

39:57.940 --> 39:58.300
Exactly.

39:58.540 --> 40:02.460
The sensation of time is literally just the sensation of constraint accumulating.

40:02.980 --> 40:06.340
And if time is the accumulation of constraint, what is space?

40:06.340 --> 40:09.280
Space is not an empty vacuum that holds objects.

40:09.980 --> 40:12.620
Space is the organization of distinguishability.

40:13.300 --> 40:16.380
Meaning, distance isn't about physical meters or miles.

40:16.780 --> 40:17.960
Distance is about effort.

40:18.600 --> 40:18.820
Yes.

40:19.380 --> 40:21.800
Distance is a measure of reconstruction cost.

40:22.620 --> 40:30.100
Two distinct points are close in space if it requires very little transformational work to map one to the other or to allow them to interact.

40:30.280 --> 40:32.180
And they are far apart if it takes a lot of work.

40:32.180 --> 40:36.700
If it requires a massive amount of transformational energy or time for them to interact, yes.

40:37.140 --> 40:41.000
Geometry itself is just the mathematical map of these distinguishability relations.

40:41.100 --> 40:45.660
So the whole universe, space-time itself, is what Flyxion calls the persistence manifold.

40:45.940 --> 40:47.080
The overarching structure.

40:47.480 --> 40:55.660
It is the joint geometry of distinguishability, which we experience as space, an accumulated constraint, which we experience as time.

40:56.460 --> 41:00.240
And mathematics, in this view, isn't just a tool we invented.

41:00.240 --> 41:07.140
No. Mathematics is the pure study of these persistence invariants, totally independent of their physical realization.

41:07.560 --> 41:10.480
Mathematics maps the absolute limits of what can persist.

41:11.260 --> 41:14.240
Space-time is the ultimate reconstructive ecology.

41:14.360 --> 41:16.660
It really elegantly ties everything together.

